<subSubSection id="42F3948DC72BFFE98BD5FA8410495C45" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0A56C706C72BFFE98BD5FA8410495C45" blockId="32.[128,654,1167,1754]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
DIAGNOSIS: The lack of a cribellum separates this species from all others except 
<taxonomicName id="CDE9BC85C72BFFE9893CFAA611D75FFC" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" genus="Zorocrates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xilitla">
<emphasis id="389D1B14C72BFFE9893CFAA611D75FFC" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Z. xilitla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it can be distinguished by the smaller median apophysis of males (
<figureCitation id="92D2DB83C72BFFE98BC8FA0E11C45FA3" box="[135,210,1493,1517]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="33.[112,159,1228,1250]" captionTargetBox="[88,1185,210,1189]" captionTargetId="figure-188@33.[88,1188,209,1194]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figs. 83–87. Zorocrates potosi, new species. 83. Left male palp, prolateral view. 84. Same, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5388245" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5388245/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">fig. 84</figureCitation>
) and the anteriorly wider epigynum of females (
<figureCitation id="92D2DB83C72BFFE98A49FA2810445C45" box="[262,338,1523,1547]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="33.[112,159,1228,1250]" captionTargetBox="[88,1185,210,1189]" captionTargetId="figure-188@33.[88,1188,209,1194]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figs. 83–87. Zorocrates potosi, new species. 83. Left male palp, prolateral view. 84. Same, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5388245" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5388245/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">fig. 86</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="42F3948DC72BFFE98BD5F9CA12275913" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="description">
<paragraph id="0A56C706C72BFFE98BD5F9CA12FF5BCE" blockId="32.[128,654,1167,1754]" lastBlockId="32.[701,1228,211,921]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
MALE: Total length 11. Coloration as in 
<taxonomicName id="CDE9BC85C72BFFE9893CF9CA11D55C09" authorityName=": Simon" authorityYear="1892" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" genus="Zorocrates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscus">
<emphasis id="389D1B14C72BFFE9893CF9CA11D55C09" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Z. fuscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Leg spination: femora: I p0-0-2, r2-0-1; II p0-1-1, r0-2-1; III r1-1-1; IV p2-0-1, r0-0-1; patellae IV r0-1-0; tibiae: I d0-0-0, p0-1-0, v4- 4-2, r0-0-0; II d0-0-0, p0-1-0, v4-4-2, r0-1-0; III r1-0-1; metatarsi: I, II p0-0-0, v2-2-2, r0-0-0; III r1-2-2; IV v3-2-2. Cribellum absent, represented only by small, fleshy, setose colulus. Retrolateral tibial apophysis strong, recurved at tip; median apophysis greatly expanded at midlength by prolaterally directed, sharp projection; tegular apophysis distally bifid (
<figureCitation id="92D2DB83C72BFFE98811FEB312C85BCE" box="[862,990,360,384]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="33.[112,159,1228,1250]" captionTargetBox="[88,1185,210,1189]" captionTargetId="figure-188@33.[88,1188,209,1194]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figs. 83–87. Zorocrates potosi, new species. 83. Left male palp, prolateral view. 84. Same, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5388245" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5388245/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">figs. 83–85</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0A56C706C72BFFE98997FE5D128F594D" blockId="32.[701,1228,211,921]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
FEMALE: Total length 12. Coloration as in male. Leg spination: femora: I p0-0-2, r0-0-0; II p0-0-1, r0-0-0; III r1-1-1; IV d1-0-1, p2-0-1, r0-0-1; patellae IV r0-1-0; tibiae: I, II d0-0-0, p0-0-0, v4-4-2, r0-0-0; III r1-0-1; metatarsi: I, II p0-0-0, v2-2-2, r0-0-0; III r1-2-2; IV v3-2-2. Cribellum absent, represented only by small, fleshy, setose colulus. Epigynum with narrow, triangular posterolateral sclerotizations, lateral margins of midpiece excavated, accompanied laterally by unsclerotized patches; spermathecae with anteromedially directed lateral ducts (
<figureCitation id="92D2DB83C72BFFE98845FD30129A594D" box="[778,908,747,771]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="33.[112,159,1228,1250]" captionTargetBox="[88,1185,210,1189]" captionTargetId="figure-188@33.[88,1188,209,1194]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figs. 83–87. Zorocrates potosi, new species. 83. Left male palp, prolateral view. 84. Same, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5388245" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5388245/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">figs. 86, 87</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
